    "Body": " Regional Executive Director BUILD - 4.2 Boston, MA Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $71,000 - $100,000 a year Benefits Health Insurance Flexible Spending Account Vision Insurance Dental Insurance Paid Time Off Qualifications Communication Skills Fundraising Recruiting Leadership Experience Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Organization Profile: : Founded in 1999, BUILD\u2019s mission is to use entrepreneurship to ignite the potential of youth in under-resourced communities and equip them for high school, college and career success. BUILD\u2019s unique program offers students a four-year entrepreneurship experience designed to develop 21st Century skills and motivate student engagement in school. Starting in 9th grade, BUILD students work with their peers and community mentors to develop business ideas, pitch to funders and launch real businesses. As students journey through high school and continue to grow their businesses, BUILD helps them explore college and career options, and assists students with the college application process. Entrepreneurship is the hook \u2013 college, career, and life success are the goals. BUILD currently serves approximately 2,000 high school students annually at programs located in the San Francisco Bay Area, Washington DC, New York City and Boston. BUILD believes in the potential of every student and is dedicated to breaking down the educational, economic and social barriers that stand in the way of their long-term success. The remarkable young men and women we serve are at the center of everything we do. Our culture thrives by embracing diversity and cross-cultural understanding. We work in a collaborative environment where flexibility, creativity and an entrepreneurial spirit are encouraged and celebrated. Kindness, empathy and respect are at the forefront of the way we treat each other, our students, our teachers and our supporters. Visit www.build.org. Position Summary: BUILD is seeking a dynamic, entrepreneurial Regional Executive Director (RED) to lead our Greater Boston office. Reporting directly to the CEO, the RED will join a learning community of REDs from the Bay Area, New York and DC and serve as a member of BUILD\u2019s National Leadership Team, working closely with BUILD leadership to influence the overall strategic direction of the national organization. The RED oversees BUILD\u2019s work with 400+ high school students in seven partner schools in Boston, including plans for further expansion statewide. The RED directs the local planning and execution of BUILD\u2019s entrepreneurship, college access and career readiness programs; fundraising and events; as well as operations and strategic planning. In order to achieve outcomes, the RED must forge strategic relationships with corporations, foundations, individuals and media outlets and deepen partnerships with community and school district leaders. Additionally, the RED hires and manages regional staff to outcomes, develops a :sustainable strategy to expand BUILD\u2019s presence in the Greater Boston region including gateway cities in Massachusetts,: and maximizes our short and long-term impact. The ideal candidate cares deeply about young people, and can inspire our students to accomplish great things. In addition, the RED will inspire our staff, board members, mentors, volunteers, and donors to advance our mission. Responsibilities: : Fundraising & External Relations (55% time allocation):: Working with the development team and board, raise the BUILD Greater Boston annual operating budget of $2M, by developing and executing a Boston regional development plan that includes corporate, foundation, individual, government and event funding streams. Manage and set high expectations for the Director of Philanthropy and the Development Team, which includes a Manager of Strategic Partnerships, Events Director, Grant Writer, and Development Associate. Serve as the external spokesperson for BUILD with key partners in the school district, local government, corporations, nonprofits, individuals, philanthropic organizations, community groups, and the media to increase visibility and brand awareness of the BUILD program.: Participate in community building activities and attend community events to deepen relationships and build connections. Manage fundraising for major events including the BUILDFest Pitch Challenge and the Entrepreneur Games by securing corporate and individual sponsorships. Recruit, manage and support Local Advisory Board members charged with supporting strategy, fundraising, advancing programmatic goals, and widening the circle of friends and supporters of BUILD. Work with new and existing corporate partners to create skills-based volunteering opportunities that involve BUILD students, in collaboration with the Manager of Strategic Partnerships. Program Management, Operations, and Expansion (45% time allocation): : Plan and execute the overall strategic direction of the BUILD Greater Boston region. Recruit, train, manage, professionally develop, and set high expectations for the regional Program Team, and ensure effective implementation of BUILD\u2019s four-year program. Develop the annual regional plan and budget in alignment with national strategic plans/programmatic priorities and direct the day-to day-work of the regional staff. Working with the Program Director and National Program Team, ensure the effective implementation of BUILD programming in the region, including program planning, implementation, evaluation and overall program quality. Oversee operations including facilities and IT, working in collaboration with the national office and external IT team. Scout and select prospective school district partnerships for regional expansion in Greater Boston, including gateway cities outside of Boston. Contribute to the organization\u2019s National Leadership Team by setting strategy and priorities and executing organizational outcomes. Qualifications:: 10+ years experience working in an educational, youth-based organization specifically serving students of color from under-resourced communities. Knowledge and deep understanding of current educational policies and practices. Proven track record of success and leadership in an entrepreneurial, fast-paced environment achieving outcomes in the following areas: Fundraising across a diversity of revenue streams, ideally with experience fundraising specifically in Boston Building and managing a Board Engaging and fostering mutually beneficial strategic relationships Developing and executing an organizational strategy to expand programming while maintaining quality Strong staff management background including recruiting and developing a high-performing, diverse team, ideally in a multi-site or regional organization Exceptional written and verbal communication and relationship building skills, with a natural ability to interact comfortably with and understand the interests of a variety of constituents and inspire enthusiasm for the organizational mission Comfort with regular regional travel and some national travel to BUILD Headquarters in the San Francisco Bay Area, or elsewhere as needed Bachelor\u2019s degree required; advanced degree preferred Compensation:: BUILD offers a competitive compensation and benefits package to all full-time employees, including medical, dental, & vision coverage, flexible spending accounts, and a 403(b) plan. In addition, BUILD employees are eligible for generous paid vacation, sick time, 10 paid holidays per year, a flexible work environment, and performance bonuses. Position Details: Location: Boston Full Time/Exempt Must have a car. Local travel will be required to partner schools in Greater Boston. Expected start date: July/August 2020 Application Instructions: To apply for this position, please submit a cover letter and resume online at www.build.org/careers:. Candidates must have both fundraising and programmatic experience in order to be considered for this position. If you do not have deep experience and a proven track record in both areas, please do not apply.: BUILD is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. At BUILD, promoting, celebrating, and supporting diversity is a core value. Individuals are considered without regard to race, gender, age, sexual orientation, sexual expression, religion, color, veteran status, disability, marital status, or ancestry. ",
